Review: when i was 6 i was embarrassed to say i’d liked this movie because i thought it was for girls

gonna have to rewatch this bc this movie is a thematic narrative first and foremost, and more subtextual than i think i was prepared for. but this got me reading the wikipedia summary for Society of the Spectacle and Simulacra and Simulation. what a dream scenario we watched tho huh!!!!!!

pretty sure i saw this in theaters as a kid. the camera is so good in this movie. the writing literally had me laugh out loud. every little sound and beat and frame is so deeply entrenched in my soul that it’s truly impossible to shake when i watch this film, it is so goofy and a timeless classic for a reason!!!
i do not know why i gave this 4 stars bc this movie is not that good but it is fine
i feel like i love this movie too much
visually pretty good but kinda toothless
honestly, this movie truly covers all its bases very cleverly and it has aged surprisingly well for it being THE meta-horror blueprint. it kinda does nothing wrong. hot take: scream is great
truly a strange movie. amazing writing, snappy, quippy. one of my fav nic cage roles. cher is GORG. it had ME moonstruck !!
incredible camerawork. a very singular film.
fun movies do the best job of conveying profound themes! we’re talking about truth here people!
i’m just excited to start telling everyone that i’ve finally seen the godfather

to be clear, i thought this movie was crafted well enough, but it only landed about half the time for me. i love upsetting imagery put to film as much as the next guy, but it did lean more gratuitous than not. the mosaic plot structure pulled me in and out. this movie undoubtedly has a vibe and i kind of appreciate that, maybe i’ll like it better upon a rewatch
